MESA and COSMIC models\npredict a similar fraction of mass gap LMXBs. However, for $M_\\mathrm{NS,\nbirth-max}\\lesssim2M_{\\odot}$ and realistic models of the disk-instability, our\nMESA models produce a dearth of mass-gap LMXBs, more consistent with\nobservations. This constraint on $M_\\mathrm{NS, birth-max}$ is independent of\nwhether low-mass BHs form at core-collapse.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2022 18:00:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-16"}
